    "discriminators": [
     "Shares the WINGS morphology (a periodic flap train, measurable via onset_periodicity), which is what makes the CATEGORY narrowable; but WINGS-CREATURE vs WINGS-BIRD is not a DSP boundary, it is a fiction boundary. A dragon wing is a slowed, layered, low-passed bird or cloth flap. semantic_only.",
     "The one defensible weak prior is scale: a large implied wing beats SLOWER (onset_rate ~0.5-3/s against a bird's 3-20/s) and carries far more low-frequency weight per flap. That is real aerodynamics - wingbeat frequency falls as wing size rises - and it is mined from the design convention. But a fairy wing inverts it completely (fast and bright), so the class is bimodal and the prior stays weak.",
     "Fairy wings are effectively WINGS-INSECT with reverb; expect them to score there."
    ],
